Narrow the cargo workspace to the client-side members only.

Upstream's monorepo workspace at npdb-0.3.0/Cargo.toml lists four members
(npdb-client, npdb-core, npdb-loadtests, npdb-server). When this recipe
builds the python client, maturin automatically downloads and resolves
Cargo.lock for ALL members - which means fetching the full server-side
dependency graph (axum, sqlx, tokio, tower, ...). That is ~100+ crates we never
link against, and a transient SSL flake on one of them fails the build.

Dropping the two server-side members shrinks the resolved graph to just
what npdb-client needs (about 30-40 crates). The on-disk npdb-server/ and
npdb-loadtests/ directories stay untouched - cargo simply ignores them now
that they're not listed.

Hopefully some fixes will land in maturin, the python package builder, to
prevent this explicit downloading, as it is e.g. not done by cargo build
and similar.

--- a/Cargo.toml
+++ b/Cargo.toml
@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@
 [workspace]
 resolver = "3"
-members = ["npdb-client","npdb-core", "npdb-loadtests", "npdb-server"]
+members = ["npdb-client", "npdb-core"]

 [workspace.package]
 authors = ["Ole Martin Ruud <ole.martin.ruud@cern.ch>"]
